function [m c] = trajectories[lats longs]
% function [m c] = trajectories[lats longs]
% 
% Description
% This function takes in the vectors for the latitude and longitude. 
% Returns two vectors, one containing the gradient and the other containing the intercepts
% Each point is trained on the three points before it, therefore, the first 3 points will not be
% trained
%
% Inputs
% LATS - The vector of latitudes of the different points
% LONGS - The vector of longitudes of the given points
% 
% Outputs
% m - The gradients of the expected paths of the points 
% c - The intercepts of the expected paths of the points
%
% Authored by Peter Mwesigwa
% Last modified Jun 18 2019
%
%

  for n = 4:size(lats)

	    x = [transpose(longs(n-2:n));[1 1 1]]
	    y = lats(n-2:n)
	    

% Using matrix algebra to calculate the line of best fit
